The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 6: The government will soon decide whether foreign players can buy stakes in Indian stock exchanges, which would make it clear if bourses can invite foreign strategic investments while divesting the brokers equity in them below 49 per cent, in line with Sebi guidelines on demutualisation. The FDI policy on the issue will soon be a reality, a senior finance ministry official said.

 Bangalore, Sept. 6: Cognizant Technology Solutions has acquired US-managed infrastructure and professional services firm Aimnet Solutions for an undisclosed sum. The network operations centre of the firm will complement Cognizants centre in Bangalore. 

 New Delhi, Sept. 6: The department of telecom has constituted a three-member committee to look into the technical aspects of the 3G spectrum to take a complete picture of the contentious issue and compliment the recommendations of Trai.

 New Delhi, Sept. 6: The appellate tribunal for electricity has quashed the West Bengal State Electricity Regulatory Commissions order asking distribution utilities to disconnect supply to the Hindalco Industries in the event of it being allowed to source power from elsewhere.

 New Delhi, Sept. 6: The government has mooted a proposal to merge dearness allowance paid to public sector employees with their basic salary, but it will have to wait till the appointment of a committee to review pay scales.




